race.comment: Tough. DHARAM SHALAA (1) impressed winning a Ballarat Maiden three back but has been plainer the two since in stronger provincial contests. Races a well-supported favourite at Kilmore two back and is better suited at this level. He rates a solid each-way play. CUT NO ICE (14) is over from Murray Bridge and peaks off two placed efforts at Gawler. The middle distance should suit her, and Meech replaces the apprentice. Has the tongue tie on for the first time and can race forward. SQUANDER (10) stepped up to this trip at Hamilton and just missed. That stacks up, and with average luck in the run, she can fight out the finish. DUHLATA (3) comes back 300m and plenty in grade. He's hard to catch but has form over this distance that reads well enough, and he'd be a hope if he produced his best.
